---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="ReviewHive is a one-person affiliate blog. Honest takes, no editorial team, no sponsored fluff."
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-zinc-50 mb-6">About This Site</h1>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none
          prose-headings:text-zinc-50
          prose-headings:font-bold
          prose-p:text-zinc-300
          prose-p:leading-relaxed
          prose-a:text-amber-400
          prose-a:no-underline
          hover:prose-a:underline
          prose-strong:text-zinc-200
          prose-li:text-zinc-300
          prose-hr:border-zinc-800">

          <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
            ReviewHive is just me — a solo developer and affiliate marketer who got tired of review sites that are either obviously SEO-farmed garbage or "media company" content with a clear agenda toward whatever pays the most.
          </p>

          <p>
            I started this as a side project. I'm a dev by trade, which means I actually read spec sheets, I understand what the numbers mean, and I have a low tolerance for marketing nonsense. I pick products I'm genuinely curious about, spend real time with them, and write up what I actually think.
          </p>

          <h2>What This Site Is</h2>
          <p>
            A solo affiliate blog. I research and write about products across tech, gear, and lifestyle. When you buy through my links I make a small commission — that's how the site pays for itself. I'm upfront about this because I'd rather you know than wonder.
          </p>
          <p>
            There's no "editorial team." There's no PR department. There are no brand deals where I agree to say nice things in exchange for money. It's one person's honest opinion, which means it's sometimes wrong and always mine.
          </p>

          <h2>How I Pick What to Cover</h2>
          <p>
            Mostly: things I was already looking into buying, or categories where I noticed the existing coverage was bad. If every review of a product is a thinly-veiled press release, I figure there's room for something more useful.
          </p>
          <p>
            I don't cover everything. I'd rather go deep on a smaller set of products than publish shallow takes on everything with an Amazon listing.
          </p>

          <h2>On Affiliate Links</h2>
          <p>
            Yes, I use them. Yes, I make money when you click and buy. No, this doesn't change what I think about the products — if anything, recommending bad stuff would kill the site faster than not recommending anything at all. The incentive structure actually works in your favor here.
          </p>
          <p>
            Full details in the <a href="/disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
          <p>
            If there's a product category you want covered, or you think I got something wrong, reach out at <a href="mailto:hello@yoursite.com">hello@yoursite.com</a>. I read everything, reply to most of it.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
